To Make Peanut Sauce Dressing: In a small bowl, combine the peanut butter, soy sauce, honey, vinegar, mustard and ginger. Mix all together and set aside. In a large saucepan over high heat, bring water to a boil; add onions and snow peas and boil for 1 minute. Rinse and drain thoroughly. Let cool. In a large bowl combine the onions, peas, turkey, bean sprouts and peanuts. Stir all together, then gently fold in peanut sauce dressing. Sprinkle with red flakes, then cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.